{"word":"Ἶρος","slug":"Ἶρος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n50902\" key=\"*)=iros\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Ἶρος</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Irus</title_>, a name given by the suitors to the Ithacan beggar Arnaeus because he carried messages (cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ἶρις</foreign>), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:18:5\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18.5</biblScope> </bibl> sq.: hence, later as Appellat., <sense id=\"n50902.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">an Irus</tr_>, i.e. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">a beggar</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg2200.tlg004:18:140\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Lib.\">Lib.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Or.\">Or.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18.140</biblScope> </bibl>: pl., <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">Ἶροι</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0062.tlg065:24\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Luc.\">Luc.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Nav.\">Nav.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">24</biblScope></bibl></cit>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}